extras.command:
cat << 'PY' > check_solution.py
import subprocess, sys, sys

# sample tests
tests = [
    ("21\n","1\n"),
    ("998244353\n","0\n"),
    ("264428617\n","32\n"),
]

for inp, expected in tests:
    p = subprocess.Popen([sys.executable, 'solution.py'], stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=True)
    out, err = p.communicate(inp)
    ok = out == expected
    print('IN:', inp.strip())
    print('OUT:', out.strip())
    print('EXP:', expected.strip())
    print('OK:', ok)
    if err:
        print('ERR:', err)
    print()
PY
